{"TopicId":159903,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Blue Origin thread.","CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-28T21:34:49Z","PageNum":95,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kerwood Floyd","CreatedById":99768,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T14:20:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635255813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat or the render is meh.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was getting ready to conclude that the render is, as you say, \u0027meh\u0027, on other grounds.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeveral of the interiors in those renders looked like they were designed for a 1 g environment, They either had a definite up/down orientation, or a lot of wasted volume for a 0 g environment. (I hope I\u0027m making myself clear)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T14:33:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also a distinct lack of emergency shutters on those large windows. That\u0027d take up additional external radius.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beccab","CreatedById":208000,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T14:45:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635258050\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299768\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerwood Floyd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, Kerwood Floyd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was getting ready to conclude that the render is, as you say, \u0027meh\u0027, on other grounds.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeveral of the interiors in those renders looked like they were designed for a 1 g environment, They either had a definite up/down orientation, or a lot of wasted volume for a 0 g environment. (I hope I\u0027m making myself clear)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey had a picnic table (with seats) and stuff that magically remained attached to the floor, so yes, it\u0027s a bad render. Bad graphics too for a 2021 promotional video\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SOXBLOX","CreatedById":204106,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T16:04:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe writing was worse. They kept blathering about all the discoveries they\u0027ll make, and how it will impact the whole world. (I mean, maybe they\u0027ll make a few. But they blew it waay out of proportion.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T16:32:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLEO science done by humans is essentially about keeping humans alive in LEO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny more basic science than that is better done sans humans, as humans mess up the microgravity environment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-26T19:22:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3512006299\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/thesheetztweetz/status/1452685954595139589\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-27T01:15:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1317112532\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SarwatNasir/status/1453021946254405641?t=OUYiGDJwNs523MCVYSUptA%26s=19\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-27T01:46:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635259520\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208000\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Beccab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, Beccab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey had a picnic table (with seats) and stuff that magically remained attached to the floor, so yes, it\u0027s a bad render. Bad graphics too for a 2021 promotional video\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not hard to bolt a table to the floor. Whether you need seats or not is a different matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what I have heard, lots of times people in microgravity establish mutual \u0022up and down\u0022 when working and talking together, simply because it is more psychologically comfortable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-10-27T01:48:40Z\u0022 title=\u002210/27/2021 01:48  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 27, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by mikegarrison\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-27T01:51:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047635\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635299202\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not hard to bolt a table to the floor. Whether you need seats or not is a different matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what I have heard, lots of times people in microgravity establish mutual \u0022up and down\u0022 when working and talking together, simply because it is more psychologically comfortable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve also heard that astronauts miss the distinction between standing and sitting in a chair. So even if you don\u0027t stick to the seat, maybe a chair would be nice. Huge open spaces, on the other hand...I\u0027d want to run some bungee ropes across.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-27T03:39:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed55664260\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Free_Space/status/1452935777638289410\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VaPaL","CreatedById":150974,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-27T11:48:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047635\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635299202\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what I have heard, lots of times people in microgravity establish mutual \u0022up and down\u0022 when working and talking together, simply because it is more psychologically comfortable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, the whole ISS has a \u0022ceiling\u0022 and a \u0022floor\u0022,\u00A0 not only for psychological reasons, but is much more confortable and easier to work if all the labels and equipments have the same orientation. IIRC the \u0022floor\u0022 is towards Earth even\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit: grammar\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-10-27T11:50:03Z\u0022 title=\u002210/27/2021 11:50  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 27, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by VaPaL\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Codraroll","CreatedById":163815,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-27T21:11:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047635\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635299202\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what I have heard, lots of times people in microgravity establish mutual \u0022up and down\u0022 when working and talking together, simply because it is more psychologically comfortable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ERendezvous with Rama\u003C/em\u003E featured this as a minor plot point, if I recall correctly. Having a defined up and down makes it easier to orient yourself, and set a mental system of reference to prevent vertigo in zero G. Imagine floating at one end of a corridor, maybe doing some work along the short wall, grabbing a handhold, and looking over your shoulder. The comfortable perspective is that you\u0027re standing at the end of a horizontal corridor, like on Earth. Slightly more unsettling is imagining that you lie at the bottom of a deep, narrow well. But if your brain somehow tricks you into believing you\u0027ve grabbed a hold to the ceiling of a tall and narrow tower shaft, you\u0027d have to take several deep breaths to let go of that handhold, and it would be hard to focus on the work you\u0027re doing. Having some surroundings telling you what is up would be a real comfort in that situation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-27T21:13:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047509\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635276122\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/26/2021 at 2:22 PM, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4090141089\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/thesheetztweetz/status/1452685954595139589\u0022 style=\u0022height:675px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen it gets around to being made that is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-27T23:27:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1834739740\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Free_Space/status/1453422985294057478\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-28T02:18:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047628\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635297338\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/26/2021 at 9:15 PM, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5214024655\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SarwatNasir/status/1453021946254405641?t=OUYiGDJwNs523MCVYSUptA%26s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:546px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s actually smart - place with no lawsuit friendly laws like the US, oil rich playboys hoping to impress friends and media control.\u00A0 Plus deniability.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-28T03:06:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047983\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635387483\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s actually smart - place with no lawsuit friendly laws like the US, oil rich playboys hoping to impress friends and media control.\u00A0 Plus deniability.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd caravans of rich people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-28T04:30:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047990\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635390391\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd caravans of rich people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Edo\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E have ATMs where you can get actual gold in lieu of cash.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-28T05:24:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635369083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163815\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Codraroll\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Codraroll said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving a defined up and down makes it easier to orient yourself, and set a mental system of reference to prevent vertigo in zero G. Imagine floating at one end of a corridor, maybe doing some work along the short wall, grabbing a handhold, and looking over your shoulder. The comfortable perspective is that you\u0027re standing at the end of a horizontal corridor, like on Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Almaz the walls, the ceiling, and the floor\u00A0 of the corridor were even painted in corresponding colors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Skylab devs preferred to think it\u0027s a tower, and the floor is the aft end.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn MOL they had a tower of cubic cubicles 2x2x2 with same floor-ceiling-walls.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, Americans prefer to hide in towers, the Russians - in tunnels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakaydos","CreatedById":101988,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-28T10:44:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635369083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163815\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Codraroll\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Codraroll said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ERendezvous with Rama\u003C/em\u003E featured this as a minor plot point, if I recall correctly. Having a defined up and down makes it easier to orient yourself, and set a mental system of reference to prevent vertigo in zero G. Imagine floating at one end of a corridor, maybe doing some work along the short wall, grabbing a handhold, and looking over your shoulder. The comfortable perspective is that you\u0027re standing at the end of a horizontal corridor, like on Earth. Slightly more unsettling is imagining that you lie at the bottom of a deep, narrow well. But if your brain somehow tricks you into believing you\u0027ve grabbed a hold to the ceiling of a tall and narrow tower shaft, you\u0027d have to take several deep breaths to let go of that handhold, and it would be hard to focus on the work you\u0027re doing. Having some surroundings telling you what is up would be a real comfort in that situation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022The enemy gate is down.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T17:53:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8292694878\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/thesheetztweetz/status/1455951296704417795?s=20\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T18:06:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwen flight hardware\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CatastrophicFailure","CreatedById":57438,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-04T05:29:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224050821\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635962766\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwen flight hardware\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter Tory gets \u003Cem\u003Ehis\u003C/em\u003E engines I would think\u2026\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u0026lt;_\u0026lt;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_dry.png\u0022 title=\u0022\u0026lt;_\u0026lt;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-05T09:04:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2026134429\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/JeffBezos/status/1456311095761637384\u0022 style=\u0022height:811px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis has, of course, been posted in the SX thread, but let\u0027s put it here as well, for posteriority and for me to point out something.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo Jeff, you do not wish NASA and SpaceX full success on this contract. If that were the case, you would not have brought this lawsuit in the first place.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegarding the respect of this court\u0027s judgement and whether he appeals and pushes this to higher courts, that remains to be seen, but I would not be surprised if he was not done with this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-05T17:30:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224047470\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635265977\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/26/2021 at 12:32 PM, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLEO science done by humans is essentially about keeping humans alive in LEO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny more basic science than that is better done sans humans, as humans mess up the microgravity environment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt should also come in handy in keeping humans alive during interplanetary voyages.\u00A0 The ISS shows a lot of issues and solutions (presumably MIR and previous Soviet space stations showed same, but NASA and Americans can easily overlook them) for spending a few months in space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-05T19:30:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224051721\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221636133434\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt should also come in handy in keeping humans alive during interplanetary voyages.\u00A0 The ISS shows a lot of issues and solutions (presumably MIR and previous Soviet space stations showed same, but NASA and Americans can easily overlook them) for spending a few months in space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure. ISS is a lab about keeping humans alive off the Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}